<topic id="performance-problems-external-processes">
  <title>External Processes</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>Performance Problems<indexterm>external processes</indexterm></indexterm>
        <indexterm>OutOfMemory</indexterm>
        <indexterm>Out Of Memory</indexterm>
        <indexterm>OutOfMemoryError</indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p>The <xref href="preferences-fo-processors.dita">Memory available to the built-in FOP</xref>
      option controls the amount of memory allocated to generate PDF output with the built-in Apache
      FOP processor. In case <ph><ph keyref="product"/></ph> throws an <i>Out Of Memory</i> error,
      go to <menucascade product="author developer editor">
        <uicontrol>Options</uicontrol>
        <uicontrol> Preferences</uicontrol>
        <uicontrol> XML</uicontrol>
        <uicontrol> XSLT-FO-XQuery</uicontrol>
        <uicontrol> FO Processors</uicontrol>
      </menucascade><menucascade product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse">
        <uicontrol>Window</uicontrol>
        <uicontrol> Preferences</uicontrol>
        <uicontrol> &lt;oXygen/></uicontrol>
        <uicontrol> XML</uicontrol>
        <uicontrol> XSLT-FO-XQuery</uicontrol>
        <uicontrol> FO Processors</uicontrol>
      </menucascade> and increase the value of the <xref href="preferences-fo-processors.dita"
        >Memory available to the built-in FOP</xref> option.</p>
    <p>For external XSL-FO processors, XSLT processors, and external tools, the maximum value of the
      allocated memory is set in the command line of the tool using the <parmname>-Xmx</parmname>
      parameter set to the Java virtual machine. </p>
  </body>
